This was the first song that I played for the band, the one that just kept coming out of me. I have really fond memories about playing this song by myself, with these little solos and breakdowns. All of it just came out pretty quickly. When I hear this song, it sounds to me like I’m enjoying this time alone. You’re not going to come in and stop this. We’re in our little hole. And you know what? We’re fine. Leave us alone. That’s what that song is about to me. We’re fine, go on about your business. Don’t take me. I won’t go…_b

We’re excited to announce our #AcousticThrills EP, out June 16th. Listen to “Empty Nest (Acoustic)” everywhere now & pre-save the EP! 🔗 in bio/stories 💙💜❤️ 

The EP features live, stripped down, and re-imagined versions of three songs from our latest record Physical Thrills, and were performed and recorded as part of @GibsonGuitar’s “The Songbook” series. 

ACOUSTC THRILLS EP TRACKLIST 
1. Scared Together (Acoustic) 
2. Empty Nest (Acoustic) 
3. Alone on a Hill (Acoustic) 

🎨: @LAD_design

This was the first time we had the pleasure of collaborating with @GibsonGuitar on their Songbook series. After building so many layers on our album Physical Thrills, it felt great to strip these songs down to their rawest form. “Empty Nest” was a bit of a challenge because we had never played it live before, but it was fun to see where the two of us could take it. . .n. 💙💜❤️
